			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">When to ditch the BoH???<a name="61773"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 9:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am currently lvl 55 and have been using the BoH in group situations since I became able to trigger the sword's effect at lvl 50. 
<br />

<br />
I am finding it quite difficult to decide at what point I should upgrade this weapon. I currently add the BoH's insta-cast Nivs Melody of Preservation to my 3 or 4 song twist during combat -  Great because it sometimes allows me to have 5 songs up at once. 
<br />
 
<br />
In my opinion the spell protection, strength increase and hp regeneration I can give to my group via this song out-weighs any potential benefits in dps or item stats I could get from another easily accessible weapon suitable for my level. For example the Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche has very appealing stats and nicer dps than the BoH. However, I reckon this still does match the overall usefulness of insta-cast Nivs to my group as a whole.
<br />

<br />
Does this rationale sound sensible? Am I overlooking anything really obvious? Would be grateful to hear some opinions on this matter.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
