			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: When to ditch the BoH???<a name="61791"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 10:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Spell protection is near useless.
<br />

<br />
The Strength buff is nice.
<br />

<br />
The HP regen is the real reason to have this song/clickie going.
<br />

<br />
However...
<br />

<br />
BDMG is Percussion.  Better percussion mod then the Epic.  Take a look at your songs that you normally twist in battle.  Will that percussion mod help you make those songs better?
<br />

<br />
Regen in most combat type situations is almost pointless unless you are non stop killing and the healer is running low.  
<br />
In combat, focus on what makes the target die faster, and what keeps your group alive longer. DS, DOTs, Debuffs are better affected by the percussion mod on the BDMG.  Resist songs, if you are singing them, and Stat boosts are better affected by the BDMG.   Your melee DPS is more effective with the BDMG.  
<br />

<br />
Regen in downtime is great though.  Break out the BoH in between fights and twist Chorus and Nivs with epic (Or beter yet, primary hand lute with a better then 1.8 mod).  Dont totaly drop the BoH, but I would use the BDMG in combat if my twist had a few drum songs in it.  
<br />
There are times later on when having that BoH can come in very handy, I would hang on to it for a while.</span></td>
