			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: When to ditch the BoH???<a name="61810"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 11:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You can keep using the BoH long after the weapon itself becomes obsolete just by juggling it in in exactly the same way you would an instrument. At some stage though, the regen you are providing becomes next to negligible in relation to the mobs you are fighting, and the additional work you are doing with the BoH might be better utilised by juggling in a horn, or the epic.
<br />

<br />
When that stage happens is something of a personal decision. For me it happened in PoP, and it felt like waving goodbye to an old friend. I had genuinely thought I might get another few expansions out of it. Depending on your own hunting habits you might find you can keep a place for it to 65 and beyond, or you might find it doesn't even last you to 60.
<br />

<br />
None of us can really tell you when to stop using it. What we can do is point out what to look for as tell-tale signs that its value is waning, and then you can make your own call on the final death nail.
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   Zel  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
